idth=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uylana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ylana</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/19/02 4:07:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5213.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://kaeryl.multimania.com/images/Ylana.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: CoM Reavers - What kind of force is really required?</span><hr size=1> Did them with a 60 SK, a 58 monk, a 54 rogue, a 60 cleric and me (60 druid). SK was pulling and monk helped splitting. You MUST have a rogue to picklock the doors and lifts. <p><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=25720"><b>Ylana Mephistaii</b></a>- 60 Hierophant of Tunare<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=66811"><b>Illine Imladris</b></a> - 46 Monk of Quellious<br><b>Bristlebane Server</b><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umiloraatwork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MiloraAtWork</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/19/02 7:46:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5213.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: CoM Reavers - What kind of force is really required?</span><hr size=1> Did it with 60 rogue 56 druid 56 chanter 53 warrior 47 warrior and 54 cleric. Had to evac twice but no deaths and got a reaver within 2 hours :) <p><center><font size=3><bold>Capulus</font></bold><br><font size=2>Milora Kinslayer</font> 56th Druid(Guild Leader)<br><font size